title: Observations
author: Pyr0Byt3
pages:
#- 




§l  "Observations"§r

    A collection of
 haikus by §4Pyr0§3Byt3§r.
#- Wake, to simply sleep

With night, squandering night with

Sleep, simply to wake.





(This one's also a word-unit palindrome)
#- The lone wolf wanders,

Long abandoned by his pack.

He cries to the moon.
#- I watch the kitten.

Those small feline eyes look back.

I'm conquered, I melt.
#- Typing in the dark;

The screen illuminates me,

As I sit alone.
#- The wandering stars,

Whom hold blackness and darkness

Forever reserved.
#- Sometimes I see you.

In my dreams, you seem so glad,

'Till you fade with dawn.
#- If one could fall out

As easily as one fell in,

"Love" would hurt no one.
#- He stares at the moon,

Hoping that somewhere out there,

She stares at it too.
#- The streetlights blur by,

Leaving fluorescent islands

On the road behind.
#- Drops fall, one... two... three...

The windshield becomes opaque,

Beneath water's veil.
#- We suffer trying

To prolong our empty lives,

Just to suffer more.
#- Out of the dark: "Click!"

As he turns the lock's tumbler,

The thief wears a grin.
#- My feet leave the ledge,

And reserved for the pavement:

My concluding kiss.
#- So many pennies

Lie lonely on the sidewalk,

Worth nobody's time.
#- That big red button,

The amount of lives that rest

Under cheap plastic.
#- He liked her; she, him.

But they'd prefer loneliness

Over rejection.
#- The sheer jittering

From my beloved caffeine

Lets me drink no more.
#- He's not desperate...

Just in a relationship

With her phone's voicemail.
#- Her bites are love notes,

Expressed not through scant paper,

But through flesh itself.
#- I fear the mirror.

Who's to say the other side

Really corresponds?
#- That piece of metal

Suffocates his ring finger

As it does his life.
#- "Sharing is caring",

But it's pronounced "piracy"

On the Internet.
#- I stare at the page.

It stares back, expressionless;

Empty, like my mind.
#- Close, never touching.

It is but an asymptote,

Their relationship.
#- How grim it must be,

Knowing with a scalpel's slip,

Slips the patient's life.
#- The one thing I hate

More than a tedious task

Is repeating it.
#- Those tetrominoes,

Possessing me whilst in wake,

Haunting me in sleep.
#- "Terms & Conditions":

No Idea what it means,

But I still agree.
#- When I've forgotten,

There's just hopelessness in ink

Smeared across my palm.
#- Whilst inflicting pain,

No blade's edge can be sharper

Than that of paper.
#- Why do lies cause shock?

The word "lie" would not exist

If all said were true.
#- 